8:
Would you look at that. I survived.
Now THAT was a scare and a half.
11:
How the hell are you still standing?
You really are a monster...
13:
So... I'd love to hear exactly who it
was that put you up to this foolish
task.
16:
Hah! You think we're the only ones
after you? You're not getting out of
this alive, you freak.
19: Yes, yes. Lovely talk. Time to die.
24:
Why do we always end up in shady
places like this?
27:
It seems like there was a mafia
clash over territory here. We
shouldn't linger long.
32:
My, what a fright. I shudder to think
how painful it would have been, had
that bullet hit me.
35:
Is this funny to you?! Do you have
any idea how much trouble you're
in, Weihu?
36:
You're going to DIE here, you
good-for-nothing bastard.
39:
I have to say, I'd really prefer if you
refrained from shooting at me. Why,
look—I'm completely unarmed!
42:
Well, this is unexpected. Who might
you be?
49:
Well, are you going to make a move, 
or what?
59:
You rescued me from quite the
pinch there. Without your timely
intervention, I'd be dead as a
doornail.
63:
Allow me to introduce myself. My
name is Weihu, and I am but a
humble office worker.
68:
An "office worker," huh? Yeah, and
I'm an indoor housecat. Nice
try—you've got that "just left the
mafia" smell all over you.
72:
Hehe. You've got quite the nose,
then.
74:
But you still helped me out. I
wonder—does that mean you have
a death wish?
78:
Er, not particularly. You just looked
like you were in trouble, and you
were right there, so...
82:
Oh, I see. In that case, I strongly
recommend you put this place far,
far behind you.
85:
Though frankly, it may already be
too late.
90:
Looks like you went and pissed off
the wrong people, huh.
93:
You lot really are relentless. I
imagine the upper echelon are in
quite the huff to get rid of me.
96:
And what's more, I see some familiar
faces among the crowd. How
nostalgic, hehe.
99:
Weihu. This is the end of the line for
you. We've got orders from up high
to get rid of you. Permanently.
102:
After breaking my back contributing
to your organization, this is the
thanks I get! How depressing.
106:
Just what exactly did you do to
these people to make them resort to
assassination in broad daylight?!
110:
It must have been that biggest flaw
of mine—I'm too passionate about
my job.
112:
I killed, killed, then for good measure
killed some more. Finally, the barrel
of a gun was pointed my way—a
cookie cutter case, really.
115: Oh, what a terrible, terrible day.
120:
Hehe... My, my... You've shot me! Ah,
the blood—the pain! It hurts so
much!
124:
This needs to END, Weihu. You're a
wild dog off its leash, and you're
bringing chaos to this city!
125:
The boss has ordered your
assassination... You've got nobody
left on your side.
127:
All alone, without a friend in the
world... You're so, so right! But that
hardly matters right now.
131:
More importantly, you've gone and
shot me! I'm bleeding! HAHA!
135:
HAHAHAHA! It's time, then! For a
glorious bloodbath where we draw
our final, dying breaths! Have you
made peace with your maker? I
HAVEN'T!
139:
Ahh, I see it! The light is starting to
fade! If I lose here, it goes out
forever—oh, please don't let it end!
Don't let me die! Oh, the HORROR!
153:
Oh dear. My apologies—I had no
intention of getting you mixed up in
this affair.
155:
You'll have to forgive me, I always let
the blood get to my head when
things get heated. It's a bad habit of
mine.
158:
Regardless, the matter at hand is
settled, and we should go our
separate ways. Forever.
161:
For that would be much, much safer
for you and yours.
171:
On a journey with no particular
destination, no doubt. But why? It
hardly concerns you.
175: Would you like to come with us?
179: Are you... inviting me to join you?
182: Stella, are you SERIOUS RIGHT NOW?
193:
This invitation comes at a most
opportune time. I was just in the
process of looking for new
employment.
195:
As you can see, things didn't work
out very well with my last job. But I
promise I wasn't lying—I can do
office work if you need any done!
200:
Just to be extra clear... You know
we're not mafia, right?
203:
Yes, yes, of course. But surely you
aren't saints—you dabble in the
occasional shady matter, do you
not? If so, I can be of use.
206:
If you need a meat shield, a bullet
sponge, I can be your man! I'll make
sure to come back alive, of course.
214:
You give me the creeps, you know
that?
219:
Haha. I get that a lot—though I
haven't the faintest idea why.
224:
I'll be watching you. You do anything
remotely suspicious, I'll kick your ass.
227:
Oohh.... Then I'll have to do my
absolute best to earn your trust
going forward, won't I?
237:
A new place to call home... Now this
is going to be interesting!
